description: Exports the contents of a Amazon Lex resource in a specified format.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the bot to export.

parameters.name: version
parameters.description: The version of the bot to export.

parameters.name: resourceType
parameters.description: The type of resource to export.

parameters.name: exportType
parameters.description: The format of the exported data.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the bot being exported.

nested_items.name: version
nested_items.description: The version of the bot being exported.

nested_items.name: resourceType
nested_items.description: The type of the exported resource.

nested_items.name: exportType
nested_items.description: The format of the exported data.
IN_PROGRESS - The export is in progress.
FAILED - The export could not be completed.

nested_items.name: failureReason
nested_items.description: If status is FAILED, Amazon Lex provides the reason that it failed to export the resource.

nested_items.name: url
nested_items.description: An S3 pre-signed URL that provides the location of the exported resource. The exported resource is a ZIP archive that contains the exported resource in JSON format. The structure of the archive may change. Your code should not rely on the archive structure.
